claim: Flublok is produced using a novel production platform in which recombinant HA is expressed in insect cells using a baculovirus expression vector system (BEVS).
explanation: Scatter and line plots showing the proportion of participants with ≥4-fold reduced hemagglutination inhibition (HI) titer to cell-based vaccine virus (egg/cell titer ratio) before and one month after repeat vaccination in Year 2, across seven different Year 1–Year 2 vaccination arms, stratified by age groups 18–44 years (panel A) and 45–64 years (panel B) and virus strains A(H3N2), A(H1N1)pdm09, B/Victoria, and B/Yamagata. The figure presents immunogenicity data comparing HI titer responses for various vaccine regimens but does not mention Flublok, insect cell expression, or a baculovirus expression vector system, and thus does not support the claim. Note: Figure is focused on serologic outcomes and does not include production method or platform details.
